Race.SpecificTitle: City of Westwego -- 6.0 Mills Renewal - M&CC - 10 Yrs.
Race.SummaryText:
City of Westwego Proposition
(Fire Department)
(Millage Renewal)
Race.FullText: Shall the City of Westwego, State of Louisiana (the "City"), under the provisions of Article VI, Sections 27(B) and 32 of the Constitution of the State of Louisiana of 1974, and other constitutional and statutory authority, continue to levy and collect a special ad valorem tax of six (6.0) mills, on all the property subject to taxation in the City (an estimated $420,000 reasonably expected at this time to be collected from the levy of the tax for one entire year), for a period of ten (10) years, beginning with the year 2025 and ending with the year 2034, inclusive, with a minimum of 50% of the annual revenues to be used for the purpose of acquiring fire department vehicles and equipment, and the remaining annual revenues to be used for the purpose of maintaining and operating fire protection services within the City, including the acquisition of the necessary equipment and facilities therefor, title to which shall be in the public?
